cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with generative models of 3D objects and their photorealistic rendering, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. The use of deep learning techniques for unsupervised learning and disentanglement of factors of variation suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of a differentiable renderer and adversarial training for image reconstruction suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
